                        A <strong class="text-primary font-semibold">Browlift</strong>, also known as a forehead lift, is a surgical procedure designed to reduce the wrinkle lines that develop horizontally across the forehead, as well as those that occur on the bridge of the nose, between the eyes. It improves frowning creases and places the eyebrows in a youthful, elevated position.
                    </p>
